description:
Under certain circumstances code assist eats too much code.
Consider the enclosed class. As a programmer, I must add a parameter to the baz call in bar to make the program correct.
Steps to reproduce: 
1. Modify the class as shown in the expected behavior section.
2. Use code assist feature to add a parameter to the baz call in the bar method.

Expected behavior: 
The code is changed to: 
baz(x.foo().foo())
I would rather it gave me 
baz(x.foo(), x.foo())

public class X {
   void bar(X x) {
      baz(x.foo());
   }

   int foo() {
      return 5;
   }

   void baz(int i, int j) {
   }
}

OB:
The code is changed to:

baz(x.foo().foo())

I would rather it gave me

baz(x.foo()x.foo())

public class X {

   void bar(X x) {
      baz(x.foo());
   }

   int foo() {
      return 5;
   }

   void baz(int i, int j) {
   }
}

EB:
The code is changed to:

baz(x.foo().foo())

I would rather it gave me

baz(x.foo(), x.foo())

public class X {

   void bar(X x) {
      baz(x.foo());
   }

   int foo() {
      return 5;
   }

   void baz(int i, int j) {
   }
}

The choice amongst one or the other should be conditioned by a keystroke (enter=replace until end, insert=replace until cursor location).
